Herein, we demonstrate a promising Li metal passivation strategy by using hybrid N‐propyl‐N‐methylpyrrolidinium bis(trifluoromethanesulfonyl)amide (Py13TFSI) and ether electrolyte. The reversibility of Li plating/stripping can be remarkably increased by the synergy between Py13TFSI ionic liquid and Li salt concentration. The hybrid electrolyte can enhance the stability of SEI layer by the in situ passivation process. The Li dendrite growth and the corrosion of Li metal anode can be efficiently restrained during cycling of Li metal batteries (Figure

1
).
